config.text: ﻿BLM Rights-of-Way Planning Tool

This tool provides mapping data for designated Section 368 energy corridors in 11 Western states

encompassing a wide range of geospatial information pertinent to corridor routing decisions.

Scroll down to learn about the tools provided.
Layer List Tool

The Layer List button groups layers by subject matter, called Operational Layers.   

You can turn layers on and off and view more information about the layers.
Source Agency

The Source Agency button series groups layers by the Federal Agency responsible for the data.  You can turn layers on and off and view more information about a layer by clicking on the button displaying an agency icon.
ReST and Item Pages

To access additional information for layers,  

in the Table of Contents, click on the ellipses (...) to the right of the layer name and select Description.  This will open either the ReST page or the Item page for the layer.
Pop-Ups
Display an informative Pop-up by clicking on a feature on the map.
MLRS

The dynamic xxxx layers have an additional link to the MLRS xxxx.

Scroll to the bottom on the pop-up and click the xxx (MLRS log) to open
Important Links

Data Dictionary for the layers contained in the Rights-of-Way Planning Tool

Geospatial Platform

This application contains datasets that are static copies of data from external sources for use in the web map,  therefore the published data may not reflect the most recent version.   For any particular dataset, the user should verify the source agency that they have the most current version.

Metadata

Some layers (hosted feature services) have additional metadata associated.

Scroll to the bottom on the pop-up and click the BLM Logo to open the PDF metadata file.
